Title: Output exact error on test import failure
Type: Bug
Units_of_Work: 1000
--
Currently if you try to load a test module to list the contents or run it and there is a syntax error in that module Lousy will barf. Instead it should output the precise error and carry on. This isn't as trivial as I first believed so it needs some deeper thought and more time spent on it.